  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project was designed to enable the UKPP to build on our project experience using the Sustainable Livelihoods Analysis in the UK to design further work, produce materials and influence policy. Two seminars were held to consolidate our understanding, one with grassroots groups and one with identified &quot;influentials&quot; to discuss the SLA as a means to overcome poverty, and produce a briefing paper.   v3  run methodology design workshop and make additions to the SLA DVD. V4 commission a writer to finalise a SLA Toolkit, v5 to do further work to complete the SLA DVD, v6 for costs of copying DVD. v7 move to England PIP.V8 Adjust budget</narrative>
  </description>
